%N A397824 Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} (1-1/p)^9 * (1 + 9/p + 9/p^2 + 1/p^3).
%C A397824 This constant, c, appears in the conjectured asymptotic formula for the eighth power moment of the Riemann zeta function on the critical line: Integral_{t=0..T} |zeta(1/2 + i*t)|^8 dt ~ (24024/16!) * c * T * log(T)^16 (Keating and Snaith, 1998; Conrey and Gonek, 2001).
%D A397824 Jonathan Keating and Nina Snaith, Random matrix theory and some zeta-function moments, lecture at Erwin Schrodinger Institute, Vienna, Sept. 1998.
%H A397824 Alain Connes, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.04022">The Riemann Hypothesis: Past, Present and a Letter Through Time</a>, arXiv:2602.04022 [math.NT], 2026. See pp. 17-18.
%H A397824 John Brian Conrey and Steven Mark Gonek, <a href="http://doi.org/10.1215/S0012-7094-01-10737-0">High moments of the Riemann zeta-function</a>, Duke Math. J., Vol. 107, No. 3 (2001), pp. 577-604; <a href="https://aimath.org/~kaur/publications/43.pdf">alternative link</a>.
